message.text:
You want to learn Japanese? Why don't you start NOW with e-learning material "NIHONGO Starter"!
日本語を学びたいあなたに朗報！eラーニング教材「にほんごにゅうもん」がJMOOCで開講中!
For more information: http://www.jpf.go.jp/e/japanese/new/1404/04-01.html

NIHONGO Starter is an English-written introductory material for Japanese-language learning on JMOOC(the Japan Massive Open Online Courses), and you can resister NOW for its CLASS 2 on facebook!
To resister: https://www.facebook.com/nihongostarter?fref=ts

Let's enjoy learning Japanese with us! 一緒に日本語勉強しませんか？

message.text:
#Hiragana Master
Say it Together! Basic Japanese Words in Japanese Alphabetical Order
Today's Word is "SE" SEIZA　#nihongo
日本の単語を五十音順にわかりやすく紹介！「せ」いざ
http://eng.nihongodecarenavi.jp/jpn/entry_4112.html

Seiza (正座, literally "proper sitting") is the Japanese term for one of the traditional formal ways of sitting, especially for sado(tea ceremony), shodo (calligraphy), ikebana (flower arranging) and some of the Japanese martial arts. Have you tried Seiza before? あなたは正座したことはありますか？足がしびれて大変です…

message.text:
Australia: Video Matsuri 2014
オーストラリア：Videoまつり2014作品募集！
3分で日本文化を紹介してください。ルールは１つ、どこかにリンゴを入れること！
Combine your Japanese ability with your creativity to make a 3 minute film! 
There is only one rule: somewhere in your film there must be an apple. 
There are no restrictions on theme or style. 
You can produce a comedy, a drama, a documentary; you can animate it, you can 
clay-mation it-the sky's the limit!
http://video-matsuri.jpf-sydney.net/
